Maria Sevilla and her autistic son Tyrone have lived in Australia for eight years . 
  She and her son face the possibility of being deported back to the Philippines after their visa expires today . 
  The single mother handed a petition to Immigration Minister Peter Dutton on Monday begging to stay in Australia . 
  Her visa application was rejected because her son would be a 'burden on the Australian health system' The 10-year-old hand delivered the petition to Mr Dutton's office in Brisbane . 
  Ms Sevilla has lived in the Queensland town of Townsville with her son since 2007 . 
  The Immigration department rejected her visa application 28 days ago . 
  Tyrone and his mother face the real possibility of deportation back to Philippines . 
 